newsitem.title: USA: Natgas futures end lower, AGAs pressure ACCESS.
newsitem.headline: Natgas futures end lower, AGAs pressure ACCESS.

text.p: NYMEX Henry Hub natgas futures, pressured by softer cash, ended lower across the board Wednesday in moderate trade, then fell further on ACCESS after an unexpectedly-large weekly AGA stock build.
September fell 2.3 cents to close at $2.03 per million British thermal units, then slipped to the $1.99-2.00 area on ACCESS. October settled 3.1 cents lower at $2.093.
"It (the AGA build) was a pretty bearish number. It could be bombs away," said one Houston-based trader, noting weaker cash prices this morning helped undermine futures during the day session.

AGA said Wednesday that U.S. gas stocks rose last week by 93 bcf to 62 percent of capacity, with the East gaining 67 bcf. The overall build was above-expectations in the 75-85 bcf range. Stocks are still 402 bcf, or 17 percent, below year-ago levels.
With injections continuing at a healthy pace and more mild weather ahead, most expected the market to remain on the defensive near-term.
But technically, prices were still range bound, with September support still at the $1.975 August 7 low and resistance at the recent $2.215 high.

Cash quotes at the U.S. Gulf Coast were off more than five cents Wednesday to the $2.00-2.05 area, almost 25 cents below August indices. Midcon pipes fell a similar amount to the mid-$1.80s, more than 25 cents below August 1 levels.
The 12-month strip slipped 1.4 cents to $2.119. NYMEX said 29,834 Henry Hub contracts traded, down from Tuesday's revised tally of 33,766.
NYMEX September Henry Hub natgas futures expire Monday, August 26.

NYMEX September Permian natgas closed seven cents lower at $1.75, while deferreds settled down by four cents but again were untraded. NYMEX said 63 Permian contracts traded, down from Tuesday's total of 30.
NYMEX September Permian natgas futures expire Wednesday August 28.
On the KCBT, September finished down by seven cents at $1.88, while deferreds ended one to six cents lower. The East/West spread widened by 1.7 cents to 19.0 cents (NYMEX premium).
KCBT September natgas futures expire Tuesday, August 27.
